
                          Variable Naming Convention 
                           for   PDM/PDU development
                                                                              -

<type> [constant][array][indirection][parameter]_variable-name


<type>
                 b    -  bit
                 B   -  BOOLEAN {used in OM}
                 c    -  character
                 d    -  double
                 f    -   float
                 F  -   FILE
                  i   -    integer
                  l   -  long
                  s   -  strcuture
                  u   -  union
                  v   -  void
                  w   -  short 
                  x   -  system defined type of variable or typedef (take
special care)



<constant>       k
                            The constant k suffix goes immediately after
whatever it is describing as
 constant;  else omitted.

<array>              a
                            if array name; else omitted.
<indirection>   p
                              if pointer to the specified type; else omitted;
Note that the indirection can go
more than one level.
<parameter>     r  - read only variable
                               w  - write only variable
                               m  - modified (read - and -write)
Used only with parameter variables within a function. Parameter variables in
the function
have extra indentifiers to show whether the parameter is read,written to, or
read and wriiten to.






